This Birds of a Feather (BoF) session offers a space for SIGCSE TS attendees to explore the interactions between a Biblical worldview and their teaching, research, and general view of technology. Our session is dual-purpose: (1) create opportunities for Christians and those interested in Christianity to connect and build a supportive community, and (2) spark thoughtful discussions on how a Christian perspective can shape ethical considerations, teaching practices, and broader challenges in CS education. Because Jesus welcomed all who came to him sincerely (Matthew 11:28) and his teaching stands within a broader biblical call to pair conviction with humility (e.g., Micah 6:8), we seek to follow His example in hosting this BoF. We recognize that conversations at the intersection of faith, identity, and ethics can involve real tension, and the Bible encourages us to meet that tension with self-reflection and invitation, rather than self-righteousness. This BoF welcomes all attendees—regardless of background, identity, belief, or experience—who want to engage respectfully in exploring how Christian perspectives can inform the ethics of technology and education. Our goal is not to prescribe uniform answers, but to provide space for honest questions and shared learning. Participants will get to reflect on how a Christian worldview informs the complexities of these topics and exchange ideas on integrating Christian perspectives into their work. We will also facilitate ways for attendees to continue the conversation post-conference through a dedicated mailing list, helping to foster ongoing connections, collaboration, and encouragement.